Controversial aphrodisiac seller Hauwa Saidu Mohammed, popularly known as Jaruma, has been allegedly arrested in Abuja. According to reports, she was arrested on Friday for drug use and the publication of fake news. The sex therapist and mother of one was reportedly arrested by billionaire Ned Nwoko for defamation and drug abuse/trafficking. Kogi: Angry Mob Sets Police Barrack Ablaze Over Slain Boy NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others Recall that the billionaire’s media team had recently posted a statement saying that Jaruma’s product was not responsible for the divorce between him and his Moroccan wife Laila Charani. The statement maintained that the reason for the divorce was Laila’s plastic surgery and her meeting with a strange man. However, the aphrodisiac seller called out the billionaire and maintained that her Kayanmata were indeed working on him as he was being controlled and manipulated by his young wife, Regina Daniels.